{
  "text": "Given this therapeutic setting, the use of stem cells or stem cell therapy is emerging as a viable option for neurorestorative stroke, especially in cases where the start time of rt-PA exceeded the ideal. The stem cell therapy promotes neuroprotection and neurorepair because of their ability to produce and secrete neurotrophic factors, and it stimulates the replacement of damaged neurons, enabling a favorable neuroimmunomodulation environment for repair [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
